    <item>
      <title>Re: Old school zones and low/no population.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=168029#M168029</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I have an idea.. I was inspired by the scavenger hunt.. maybe someone else has suggested it before, but if they did, I don't know about it.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;How about having&amp;nbsp;an epic quest?&amp;nbsp; Not for a weapon, but for experience, skills, money, faction, whatever.&amp;nbsp; It is a quest that will take you all over Norrath at the appropriate levels.&amp;nbsp; It&amp;nbsp;will&amp;nbsp;evolve as new expansions are added.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;It starts when you are level 1.&amp;nbsp; Your guildmaster mentions it to you when you hand him the note.&amp;nbsp; Maybe something like, "when you are older, go see (npc) in (zone) for the next part of your adventure."&amp;nbsp; So at a certain level, let's say 10, you go see the npc in another zone (not too far away).&amp;nbsp; That npc has a task for you, it could be anything really, but it's something that can be solo'd by ANY race and class (whether it be tradeskill related, collect x amount of some item, look for ground spawns, speak to other npc's etc. etc).&amp;nbsp; When you complete that task, he gives you a reward and tells you to go see another npc when you are older, and so on and so on.&amp;nbsp; If you go to that npc before the required level, the npc tells you to come back when you are older.&amp;nbsp; The tasks you are given and npc's you are sent to could be totally random, with lots of different possibilities, so that each person will get a unique quest.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;When a player reaches level 70, the have a final task.. something hard this time.&amp;nbsp; Your reward could be one of many.. there is no set reward.&amp;nbsp; It would depend on the path you took for your epic quest.&amp;nbsp; But all possible rewards should be something cool..&amp;nbsp; not a&amp;nbsp;crappy weapon that will be junk 6 months later.&amp;nbsp; I can't think of anything off the top of my head but you get the idea.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Edited to add that you get a reward for each task :)&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by Frangellica on &lt;span class=date_text&gt;04-11-2005&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=time_text&gt;01:08 PM&lt;/span&gt;</description>
