    <item>
      <title>Re: Old school zones and low/no population.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=168142#M168142</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Instead of using instanced zones, what about using morphing zones?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What I mean by a morphing zone is:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Look at Gukta and Oggok.&amp;nbsp; Gutka is the Froglok Home and former home of the Trolls.&amp;nbsp; Oggok is the Ogre home city.&amp;nbsp; When certain conditions are met in The Feerott and Innothule Swamp, a permanent but minor&amp;nbsp;change occurs to the zone.&amp;nbsp; After 10 or 20 minor changes, a major change occurs.&amp;nbsp; This would keep the content in the zones changing and would keep players interested in seeing what new happened.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Some examples of changes could be:&amp;nbsp;When a certain number of lizards are killed at the camps in the Feerott, one of the lizard camps disappears or maybe more lizards show up to reinforce the camp; In Innothule Swamp, when enough mobs are killed within a certain distance to the Feerott Zone Line, a small Ogre Fort appears with Ogres that are there to either help secure the Feerott from intrusion by the Frogloks or to help the Trolls regain their home city.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Regarding the stories that are written by SOE(?) and available in game: Why not have a bunch of quests surrounding those stories?&amp;nbsp; When Grobb fell, some stone was stolen.&amp;nbsp; Why not have 40 or 50 quests made available to players which will run them around and advance the story line?&amp;nbsp; In some cases, why not have opposing quests where players can either help the Trolls or the Frogloks and as each quest gets completed (or gets completed a specific number of times), the story changes and new quests are released.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Back when I first start playing EQ (a different account on a different server from where I am now), the biggest complaint I heard from players was that this game is an MmoRPG...emphasis on the RPG.&amp;nbsp; What peeps wanted back then was some way to influence the world.&amp;nbsp; As things stand, there really is no way to influence the storyline of EQ at all.&amp;nbsp; Morden Rasp may be the person who's visions all Norrathians will eventually follow, but why not allow the players to alter the course that Norrath takes in small ways?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Arch&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
