&lt;DIV&gt;Arch&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I LOVE this idea (thats why I gave it 5 stars...) htere are already some player triggered zone changes, like the sonic wolf/ grimling (is it grimlings?) war in Hollowshade, and the Thurgadin/ giant war that is the climax of the Coldain Ring quest.&amp;nbsp; But these are temporary; when they are over, things are back to normal.&amp;nbsp; But a reactive game would be great, and technically feasible.&amp;nbsp; It would mean that each server would be in a different state at any given moment.&amp;nbsp; On server A, there have not been enough kills of Emperor Crush, so there are orc raids near Kelethin every night.&amp;nbsp; On server B, things are more or less normal.&amp;nbsp; On server C, killing Crushie has been very popular, and so the camp at Orc Hill has been taken over; the wood elves who now control it offer special quests and rewards to those who go into Crushbone on missions...but the orcs have prevailed on Dvinn to bring in some dark elf necromancers in a last ditch effort to save their home, so the zone is tougher now.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;Ideally each "state" of a zone should offer similar risk/ reward balance, and a "trivial kills don't count" rule would prevent level 40s from whacking green Crush over and over to trigger a state change.&amp;nbsp; Players might have competing agendas... I want the orcs to be ahead because that state gives better warrior drops from the orc raiders (or just because I'm evil), while you want the elves to win because there's a nice enchanter item that drops from those dark elves (or because Kelethin is your home, and it's role playing your character to want to protect it).&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Cricketbane theCurious&lt;BR&gt;Froglok Shaman on Fennin Ro&lt;BR&gt;Fatale guild co-leader&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
